      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "### Operator Flow\n- Start in **Overview Dashboard** for fleet posture and active failure clusters.\n- Use this board after you know which worker or failure shape you are investigating.\n- Filter to a worker first.\n- Start with **Last Verification**, **Verification Age**, **Current Sync Age**, **Runtime Snapshot Labels**, and the restart counters.\n- Use **Current Failure Labels** for active breakage and **Fleet Last Failure Classes** for the most recent failure shape, even if the worker recovered.\n- Use **Fleet Workload Shapes** to confirm the exact load mode, replay dataset, write rate, payload size, and concurrency behind the incident.\n- Use **Fleet Runtime Snapshot States** and **Fleet Runtime Snapshot Counts** to separate healthy telemetry from genuinely unhealthy runtime snapshots.\n- Use **Active Failure x Runtime Counts** and **Active Failure x Runtime Workers** to see which active failure signatures also have unhealthy runtime snapshots.\n- If the worker is bad, jump to **Selected Worker**, **Worker Summaries**, **Operator Help**, or **Prompt Bundle** in the dashboard links.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Runbook",
      "type": "text"
    },
